### The Big Idea: Process-Relative Orientation
Time = gap between mathematical expectation and observed reality.
Not "what time is it?" but "should that process be done by now?"
705× more detectable internally than externally. The fisherman at the bar.

### Federation: 1-Bit Miracle
Even 1 bit of shared information (sign pattern) creates measurable cross-fleet correlation.
The sign is STRUCTURE (max-cut), not magnitude. Structure > magnitude for coordination.
4-agent fleets can federate indefinitely through 10-byte/step bridges.

